### BI Dashboard Backend API - HTTP Client Examples

These examples can be used with:
- VS Code REST Client extension
- Postman
- Thunder Client
- Any HTTP client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000
@contentType = application/json

---

## Health & Status

### ✓ Health Check
GET @baseUrl/health

---

### ✓ Get API Info
GET @baseUrl/

---

## Database Schema

### ✓ Get Full Database Schema
GET @baseUrl/api/schema

---

### ✓ List All Tables
GET @baseUrl/api/tables

---

### ✓ Get Sales Table Info
GET @baseUrl/api/tables/sales

---

### ✓ Get Employees Table Info
GET @baseUrl/api/tables/employees

---

## Analytics

### ✓ Get Sample Data from Sales
GET @baseUrl/api/analytics/sample?table_name=sales&limit=10

---

### ✓ Get Sample Data from Employees  
GET @baseUrl/api/analytics/sample?table_name=employees&limit=5

---

### ✓ Get Column Info for Sales Table
GET @baseUrl/api/analytics/columns/sales

---

### ✓ Get Column Info for Employees Table
GET @baseUrl/api/analytics/columns/employees

---

## Dashboard Generation

### ✓ Simple Dashboard - Total Revenue by Region
POST @baseUrl/api/dashboard/generate
Content-Type: @contentType

{
  "query": "Show me total revenue by region",
  "limit": 100
}

---

### ✓ Dashboard with Filters
POST @baseUrl/api/dashboard/generate
Content-Type: @contentType

{
  "query": "Show me total revenue by region",
  "filters": {
    "region": "North"
  },
  "limit": 100
}

---

### ✓ Dashboard - Monthly Trends
POST @baseUrl/api/dashboard/generate
Content-Type: @contentType

{
  "query": "Display monthly sales trend over the past quarter",
  "limit": 100
}

---

### ✓ Dashboard - Top Products
POST @baseUrl/api/dashboard/generate
